# Import Eternis's Anonymizer SLM into Ollama.
#
# 1. Download a GGUF from the collection:
#      https://huggingface.co/collections/eternisai/anonymizer-model-series
#    (the 1.7B or 4B variant is the sweet spot; quantize to Q4_K_M for laptops).
# 2. Put the .gguf next to this file (or fix the FROM path).
# 3. Build it:
#      ollama create anonymizer-slm -f models/anonymizer-slm.Modelfile
# 4. Use it:
#      ANONPROXY_DETECTORS=regex,anonymizer-slm python -m anonproxy serve
#
# Anonproxy uses only the model's *detections* and applies its own deterministic
# surrogates, so the exact replacement style of the model doesn't affect
# consistency or reversibility.

FROM ./anonymizer-slm-4b-q4_k_m.gguf

PARAMETER temperature 0
PARAMETER num_ctx 4096

# The model was trained to return a replace_entities tool call; keep it terse.
SYSTEM """You identify personal/sensitive entities in the user's text and return a replace_entities tool call listing each original span to replace. Return only the tool call."""
